<section>
  <div>
    <h1>Data and javascript attributes</h1>
    <p>Attributes often used with a script.</p>
    <p><strong>data - </strong>Specifies URL of the resource to be used by the object element.</p>
    <p>Can be used with: &lt;object&gt;</p>
    <p><strong>data-* - </strong>Used to store embeded data, private to the page.</p>
    <p>Can be used with: Global(all elements)</p>
    <p><strong>onclick - </strong>Script that runs when the element is clicked.</p>
    <p>Can be used with: All visible elements.</p>
    <p><strong>onmouseover - </strong>Script that runs when the element is hovered.</p>
    <p>Can be used with: All visible elements.</p>
    <p><strong>onmousedown - </strong>Script that runs when the mousebutton is clicked down.</p>
    <p>Can be used with: All visible elements.</p>
    <p><strong>onmouseup - </strong>Script that runs then the mousebutton is released.</p>
    <p>Can be used with: All visible elements.</p>
    <p><strong>onload - </strong>Script that runs when the element is loaded.</p>
    <p>Can be used with: &lt;body&gt;, &lt;iframe&gt;, &lt;img&gt;, &lt;input&gt;, &lt;link&gt;, &lt;script&gt;, &lt;style&gt;</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>Visual example</h3>
    <p>Functions which will display an alert when the button is clicked and hovered.</p>
    <button onclick="onclickExample()">Click me</button>
    <button onmouseover="onmouseoverExample()">Hover me</button>
    <hr>
    <p>Embeded data attributes.</p>
    <p>Click the li items to get the alert showing the embeded data.</p>
    <ul>
      <li onclick="showDetails(this)" data-fruit-color="yellow">Banana</li>
      <li onclick="showDetails(this)" data-fruit-color="orange">Orange</li>
      <li onclick="showDetails(this)" data-fruit-color="red">Apple</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>Code example</h3>
    <pre>
      <code>
        /* Html */
          &lt;button onclick="onclickExample()"&gt;Click me&lt;/button&gt;
          &lt;button onmouseover="onmouseoverExample()"&gt;Hover me&lt;/button&gt;

          &lt;ul&gt;
            &lt;li onclick="showDetails(this)" data-fruit-color="yellow">Banana&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;li onclick="showDetails(this)" data-fruit-color="orange">Orange&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;li onclick="showDetails(this)" data-fruit-color="red">Apple&lt;/li&gt;
          &lt;/ul&gt;

        /* Javascript */
          function showDetails(fruit){
            var fruitColor = fruit.getAttribute("data-fruit-color");
            alert("The color of the " + fruit.innerHTML + " is " + fruitColor + ".");
          }
      </code>
    </pre>
  </div>
</section>
